- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with hate speech detection in memes, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper uses visual information to detect hate speech in memes.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with hate speech spread through social networks.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with multimedia documents (memes) that combine images and text.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses a multi-layer perceptron to detect hate speech in memes.
